A: You are using the same iterator in each loop iteration. You should use the iterator of the current DataSnapshot in each loop iteration.
Here is the corrected code:
names=new ArrayList<>();
rootRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
    @Override
    public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot dataSnapshot) {
        Iterator<DataSnapshot> iterator = dataSnapshot.getChildren().iterator();
        while(iterator.hasNext()) {
            DataSnapshot childSnapshot = iterator.next();
            names.add(childSnapshot.getValue(String.class));
        }
        Toast.makeText(signup.this,""+names,Toast.LENGTH_LONG).show();
    }

    @Override
    public void onCancelled(DatabaseError databaseError) {
        // Handle error
    }
});

In this code, I've created an iterator for the children of the dataSnapshot. Then, in each loop iteration, I'm getting the next child snapshot and adding its value to the names list.

